cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with processing video data using deep neural networks. It could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories as it introduces a new type of network and an optimization method for converting pre-trained networks. Additionally, it could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it proposes a more efficient way of processing data. Finally, it could also be classified under multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with video data.
